I think you should probably make this a PR, since the requested behavior is pretty well fulfilled, the only ambiguity from the issue is  the name of `toggle_inherited`, which is a good name.

I would not implement this kind of abstraction. It just makes the code more confusing, I will have to read the source to figure out what the method does instead of looking at its name. Toggling the enum with 3 states doesn't make sense at all. Most of the time users will hide/unhide base on some condition then they just
```rust
visility = if should_show {
   Visibility::Visible
} else {
   Visibility::Hidden
}
```
